    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Ephesians",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 5,
        "summary": "The Saints are exhorted to avoid uncleanness and walk uprightly\u2014Husbands and wives should love each other.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Be ye therefore followers of God, as dear children;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0imitators. 1\u00a0Cor. 11:1; Philip. 3:17 (13\u201321). TG\u00a0God, the Standard of Righteousness; Jesus Christ, Exemplar.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And walk in love, as Christ also hath loved us, and hath given himself for us an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweetsmelling savour.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 8:3.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Self-Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 105
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 8:21; Lev. 1:9.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 139
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But fornication, and all uncleanness, or covetousness, let it not be once named among you, as becometh saints;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastity; Fornication; Sexual Immorality.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Saints.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Neither filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not convenient: but rather giving of thanks.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Filthiness.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Levity.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 5:2; Matt. 12:36.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For this ye know, that no whoremonger, nor unclean person, nor covetous man, who is an idolater, hath any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastity; Whore.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Uncleanness.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Inheritance; Worthiness.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 117
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let no man deceive you with vain words: for because of these things cometh the wrath of God upon the children of disobedience.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Indignation of.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Be not ye therefore partakers with them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For ye were sometimes darkness, but now are ye light in the Lord: walk as children of light:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Children of Light.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 12:2.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "(For the fruit of the Spirit is in all goodness and righteousness and truth;)",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Proving what is acceptable unto the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 49:6; Ps. 1:1 (1\u20132); Prov. 1:10 (10\u201319).",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Darkness, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reproof.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done of them in secret.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But all things that are reproved are made manifest by the light: for whatsoever doth make manifest is light.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore he saith, Awake thou that sleepest, and arise from the dead, and Christ shall give thee light.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Light of the World; Light [noun].",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "See then that ye walk circumspectly, not as fools, but as wise,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Redeeming the time, because the days are evil.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore be ye not unwise, but understanding what the will of the Lord is.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And be not drunk with wine, wherein is excess; but be filled with the Spirit;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Drunkenness; Word of Wisdom.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Temperance.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Speaking to yourselves in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Singing.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 3:15.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Giving thanks always for all things unto God and the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Thanksgiving.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Submitting yourselves one to another in the fear of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reconciliation.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as unto the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Continuing Courtship in.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Esth. 1:20 (20\u201322). TG\u00a0Submissiveness.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church: and he is the saviour of the body.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Husbands.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Head of the Church.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Church.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore as the church is subject unto Christ, so let the wives be to their own husbands in every thing.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also loved the church, and gave himself for it;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Patriarchal.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Love within; Love.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Continuing Courtship in.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of water by the word,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sanctification.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Purification.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That he might present it to himself a glorious church, not having spot, or wrinkle, or any such thing; but that it should be holy and without blemish.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "So ought men to love their wives as their own bodies. He that loveth his wife loveth himself.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For no man ever yet hated his own flesh; but nourisheth and cherisheth it, even as the Lord the church:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Body, Sanctity of.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For we are members of his body, of his flesh, and of his bones.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 6:15.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and shall be joined unto his wife, and they two shall be one flesh.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Celestial; Unity.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 116
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "This is a great mystery: but I speak concerning Christ and the church.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mysteries of Godliness.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Nevertheless let every one of you in particular so love his wife even as himself; and the wife see that she reverence her husband.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 94
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Courtesy; Respect.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 117
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 121
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}